  "prompt": "I've only heard one song by Jackson Browne which I totally loved! 'Late for the sky'! Can anyone recommend me more Jackson Browne songs? Even albums?",
  "response": "Absolutely! Jackson Browne is a fantastic singer-songwriter with a rich catalog of music. If you loved \"Late for the Sky,\" here are some more songs and albums you might enjoy:\n\n**Songs:**\n1. \"These Days\"\n2. \"Running on Empty\"\n3. \"The Pretender\"\n4. \"Doctor My Eyes\"\n5. \"For a Dancer\"\n6. \"Fountain of Sorrow\"\n7. \"Stay\"\n8. \"Rosie\"\n9. \"Sky Blue and Black\"\n10. \"Before the Deluge\"\n\n**Albums:**\n1. **Jackson Browne (1972)** - Also known as \"Saturate Before Using,\" includes hits like \"Doctor My Eyes\" and \"Rock Me on the Water.\"\n2. **For Everyman (1973)** - Contains classics like \"These Days\" and \"For Everyman.\"\n3. **Late for the Sky (1974)** - The album you already love; it\u2019s highly regarded for its depth and lyrical beauty.\n4. **The Pretender (1976)** - Features popular songs like \"The Pretender\" and \"Here Come Those Tears Again.\"\n5. **Running on Empty (1977)** - A unique mix of live recordings, which includes \"Running on Empty\" and \"The Load-Out/Stay.\"\n6. **Hold Out (1980)** - Includes tracks like \"Boulevard\" and \"That Girl Could Sing.\"\n7. **Lawyers in Love (1983)** - Known for songs like \"Lawyers in Love\" and \"Tender Is the Night.\"\n\nThese selections should give you a great overview of Jackson Browne's work and musical style! Enjoy exploring his discography.",
